1247
00:54:04.333 --> 00:54:06.643
She's done versions of that to me

1248
00:54:06.667 --> 00:54:08.125
a million times since then.

1249
00:54:09.250 --> 00:54:10.792
But here I am.

1250
00:54:11.542 --> 00:54:13.101
By her side.

1251
00:54:13.125 --> 00:54:16.809
Or to the side. you know.
a few steps behind.

1252
00:54:16.833 --> 00:54:18.559
[chuckles]

1253
00:54:18.583 --> 00:54:20.125
And you'd rather be out front?

1254
00:54:21.375 --> 00:54:23.958
Maybe you should tell her what you want.

1255
00:54:24.750 --> 00:54:26.309
What. like you do?

1256
00:54:26.333 --> 00:54:28.059
Like everyone else does?

1257
00:54:28.083 --> 00:54:30.226
Benji. I want you to meet
some of the people

1258
00:54:30.250 --> 00:54:32.559
I worked with at <i>Runway</i>
a gazillion years ago.

1259
00:54:32.583 --> 00:54:34.309
This is. um. Nigel Kipling.

1260
00:54:34.333 --> 00:54:36.143
- Nigel.
- Pleasure.

1261
00:54:36.167 --> 00:54:38.268
And that's Andy...

1262
00:54:38.292 --> 00:54:39.809
- something or other.
- Okay. Andy.

1263
00:54:39.833 --> 00:54:42.143
- Sachs.
- Sorry. can't remember. Sachs.

1264
00:54:42.167 --> 00:54:43.226
- Hi. hi.
- [Benji] Andy. Hi.

1265
00:54:43.250 --> 00:54:46.934
Oh. God. That dress... that is po-pow!

1266
00:54:46.958 --> 00:54:48.726
No. I really hate po-pow. No. no. no.

1267
00:54:48.750 --> 00:54:50.393
Sorry. I'm sorry.

1268
00:54:50.417 --> 00:54:53.667
It's very nice. Not couture.
not custom. but it is nice.

1269
00:54:54.542 --> 00:54:55.643
Say. are you the gal

1270
00:54:55.667 --> 00:54:58.351
who wrote that piece
in <i>Runway</i> about my gal. Emily?

1271
00:54:58.375 --> 00:55:00.059
- Yes. I am.
- Oh. my God.

1272
00:55:00.083 --> 00:55:01.143
I gotta thank you.

1273
00:55:01.167 --> 00:55:05.559
- Really?
- That was so intriguing to me.

1274
00:55:05.583 --> 00:55:07.268
The writing?

1275
00:55:07.292 --> 00:55:08.184
Photos.

1276
00:55:08.208 --> 00:55:10.143
- The photos were so good.
- The subject.

1277
00:55:10.167 --> 00:55:11.417
- Right?
- [glass shatters]

1278
00:55:12.208 --> 00:55:14.351
[♪ dramatic music playing]

1279
00:55:14.375 --> 00:55:15.458
[Miranda screams]

1280
00:55:16.333 --> 00:55:18.018
[guests gasping]

1281
00:55:18.042 --> 00:55:19.458
Oh. my God!

1282
00:55:20.375 --> 00:55:22.101
Is there a doctor?

1283
00:55:22.125 --> 00:55:23.875
Dad? Dad?

1284
00:55:25.042 --> 00:55:27.434
- Oh. my God. Dad.
- Irv.

1285
00:55:27.458 --> 00:55:28.667
Dad?

1286
00:55:32.417 --> 00:55:34.750
[♪ Somber music playing]

1287
00:56:00.042 --> 00:56:01.393
Got a lot to think about.

1288
00:56:01.417 --> 00:56:03.518
A day like today really
puts things in perspective

1289
00:56:03.542 --> 00:56:05.292
how fast time moves.

1290
00:56:06.042 --> 00:56:08.393
How we gotta focus on what's important.

1291
00:56:08.417 --> 00:56:09.643
And priorities.

1292
00:56:09.667 --> 00:56:11.851
- [Miranda] Mm-hmm.
- My father loved <i>Runway.</i>

1293
00:56:11.875 --> 00:56:14.268
- you know.
- Yes. he did.

1294
00:56:14.292 --> 00:56:15.726
So did your grandfather.

1295
00:56:15.750 --> 00:56:16.809
Yeah.

1296
00:56:16.833 --> 00:56:18.125
He hired me. you know.

1297
00:56:19.208 --> 00:56:22.768
And when he passed everything
over to Irv... [chuckles]

1298
00:56:22.792 --> 00:56:24.851
- Yeah.
- We were the same age.

1299
00:56:24.875 --> 00:56:27.601
We worked so closely.

1300
00:56:27.625 --> 00:56:28.851
Yeah. Right.

1301
00:56:28.875 --> 00:56:29.875
Now it's me and you.

1302
00:56:31.125 --> 00:56:33.750
And I look forward
to carrying that football

1303
00:56:34.250 --> 00:56:35.667
into the end zone together.

1304
00:56:37.750 --> 00:56:38.934
[sighs]

1305
00:56:38.958 --> 00:56:43.018
The end zone. So beautifully put.

1306
00:56:43.042 --> 00:56:45.042
[mourners chattering]

1307
00:56:52.875 --> 00:56:54.042
Isn't this awful?

1308
00:56:55.583 --> 00:56:57.059
I can't believe this is happening.

1309
00:56:57.083 --> 00:56:58.309
It's terribly sad.

1310
00:56:58.333 --> 00:56:59.518
Yes. it is very sad.

1311
00:56:59.542 --> 00:57:02.125
Somehow. Dolce dressed everyone here.

1312
00:57:02.750 --> 00:57:05.476
This entire funeral is their fall '26.

1313
00:57:05.500 --> 00:57:07.309
I mean. they must've driven
to everyone's houses

1314
00:57:07.333 --> 00:57:08.643
flinging out freebies. no doubt.

1315
00:57:08.667 --> 00:57:11.809
- Bloody Domenico. So sly.
- [chuckles]

1316
00:57:11.833 --> 00:57:13.268
He'll do anything to get back at me

1317
00:57:13.292 --> 00:57:15.250
since I put Kendall in the finale of '24.

1318
00:57:16.250 --> 00:57:17.726
Isn't she the greatest?

1319
00:57:17.750 --> 00:57:20.226
He's been chomping at the bit
for vengeance.

1320
00:57:20.250 --> 00:57:21.809
- [Benji] Yeah. [chuckles]
- Over Kendall.

1321
00:57:21.833 --> 00:57:23.625
I can't believe there's
someone named Candle.

1322
00:57:28.417 --> 00:57:30.393
What's Jay gonna do? Do you know?

1323
00:57:30.417 --> 00:57:32.434
Do we have any idea what
he's gonna do with <i>Runway</i>?

1324
00:57:32.458 --> 00:57:34.518
No. no. I have no idea.

1325
00:57:34.542 --> 00:57:36.601
but. I mean. you've seen the man.

1326
00:57:36.625 --> 00:57:38.684
He's not exactly a fashion icon.

1327
00:57:38.708 --> 00:57:41.750
He's dressed head to toe
in performance synthetics.

1328
00:57:42.250 --> 00:57:43.226
Throw a match at him

1329
00:57:43.250 --> 00:57:45.167
and he'll go up like
a Christmas tree in March.

1330
00:57:46.083 --> 00:57:48.125
We're gonna be okay. right?

1331
00:57:48.708 --> 00:57:50.351
<i>Runway</i> is still valuable. right?

1332
00:57:50.375 --> 00:57:52.583
I mean. even without Irv.
They know that. right?

1333
00:57:53.542 --> 00:57:55.750
Sorry. So aggressively rhetorical.

1334
00:57:56.708 --> 00:57:58.059
You know. I have no idea.

1335
00:57:58.083 --> 00:58:00.042
We're just going to have to soldier on.

1336
00:58:00.917 --> 00:58:02.500
[horns honking]

1337
00:58:03.708 --> 00:58:06.393
[Nigel] <i>Runway Italy</i>
helped establish Milan

1338
00:58:06.417 --> 00:58:08.601
as one of fashion's most important

1339
00:58:08.625 --> 00:58:10.476
bases of operation.

1340
00:58:10.500 --> 00:58:14.500
which is why we can own this

1341
00:58:15.083 --> 00:58:16.500
the Brera Academy.

1342
00:58:17.042 --> 00:58:18.518
We're going to have a custom runway

1343
00:58:18.542 --> 00:58:20.434
that will be for fashion

1344
00:58:20.458 --> 00:58:21.934
as well as musical acts.

1345
00:58:21.958 --> 00:58:23.518
The whole evening is going to kick off

1346
00:58:23.542 --> 00:58:26.351
with one of Miranda's trademark speeches.

1347
00:58:26.375 --> 00:58:28.309
This one will be about the intermingling

1348
00:58:28.333 --> 00:58:30.809
of <i>Runway</i> and Italian couture.

1349
00:58:30.833 --> 00:58:32.518
I'm almost finished
with the speech. by the way.

1350
00:58:32.542 --> 00:58:34.851
It will be in your inbox
by the end of the week.

1351
00:58:34.875 --> 00:58:35.893
Yes. Marta?

1352
00:58:35.917 --> 00:58:38.018
Yeah. this thing
with Irv dying and all that.

1353
00:58:38.042 --> 00:58:39.559
when do we find out if things
are changing around here?

1354
00:58:39.583 --> 00:58:41.101
Yeah. what's Jay's plan for the magazine?

1355
00:58:41.125 --> 00:58:42.143
Is he taking over?

1356
00:58:42.167 --> 00:58:43.768
I mean. does he even like fashion?

1357
00:58:43.792 --> 00:58:44.851
I mean. he wears Drakkar Noir.

1358
00:58:44.875 --> 00:58:46.226
- No. he doesn't.
- Oh. my God.

1359
00:58:46.250 --> 00:58:48.601
I'd like to talk about the looks

1360
00:58:48.625 --> 00:58:52.934
that we're going to feature
in the Brera Academy show.

1361
00:58:52.958 --> 00:58:55.833
Some of the bodies
are very interesting. very...

1362
00:58:57.417 --> 00:58:59.351
body... negative.

1363
00:58:59.375 --> 00:59:00.559
[clears throat]

1364
00:59:00.583 --> 00:59:05.667
No. don't tell me.
I know this. Body positive.

1365
00:59:07.667 --> 00:59:10.768
[sighs] But why. really?
When you think a...

1366
00:59:10.792 --> 00:59:12.184
[Dirk] Oh. my God. He's here.

1367
00:59:12.208 --> 00:59:13.393
[Amari gasps]

1368
00:59:13.417 --> 00:59:15.708
[staff member 1] Yeah.
that's. like. our new owner.

1369
00:59:26.208 --> 00:59:27.792
[♪ Tense music playing]

1370
00:59:29.750 --> 00:59:31.684
Always loved your office.

1371
00:59:31.708 --> 00:59:33.518
Can't get views like this anymore.

1372
00:59:33.542 --> 00:59:34.434
[Miranda] Mmm.

1373
00:59:34.458 --> 00:59:37.893
And the size. I mean. wow.

1374
00:59:37.917 --> 00:59:40.226
[Miranda] I remember
you coming to the offices

1375
00:59:40.250 --> 00:59:42.042
as a kid with your father

1376
00:59:43.208 --> 00:59:45.184
and your little lacrosse stick.

1377
00:59:45.208 --> 00:59:47.768
tossing that ball up all around.

1378
00:59:47.792 --> 00:59:49.309
I broke a vase.

1379
00:59:49.333 --> 00:59:51.601
Did you? I don't remember.

1380
00:59:51.625 --> 00:59:53.643
Anyway. sorry it took me a while

1381
00:59:53.667 --> 00:59:56.726
to stop by or call you back.

1382
00:59:56.750 --> 00:59:58.184
We barely noticed.

1383
00:59:58.208 --> 01:00:01.059
But now I'm ready to get ducks in rows.

1384
01:00:01.083 --> 01:00:04.875
kick some concepts around
with you. check boxes. Lunch?

1385
01:00:05.583 --> 01:00:08.434
- Now?
- Bad time? You slammed?

1386
01:00:08.458 --> 01:00:09.726
No. not at all.

1387
01:00:09.750 --> 01:00:12.309
I'll just get someone
to make a reservation at...

1388
01:00:12.333 --> 01:00:13.518
Oh. cafeteria's fine.

1389
01:00:13.542 --> 01:00:16.476
I have a couple calls
that I should return anyway.

1390
01:00:16.500 --> 01:00:19.375
Um. I will see you there in ten.

1391
01:00:24.708 --> 01:00:26.042
Amari?

1392
01:00:27.708 --> 01:00:28.601
Yes?

1393
01:00:28.625 --> 01:00:30.542
We have a cafeteria?

1394
01:00:31.083 --> 01:00:32.500
- Oh. yes.
- Really?

1395
01:00:35.375 --> 01:00:36.375
[phone chimes]

1396
01:00:38.792 --> 01:00:40.000
Cafeteria?

1397
01:00:41.458 --> 01:00:44.018
She's never even been to that floor.

1398
01:00:44.042 --> 01:00:45.333
[elevator bell dings]

1399
01:00:48.292 --> 01:00:49.351
It's frozen again.

1400
01:00:49.375 --> 01:00:50.768
[staff chattering]

1401
01:00:50.792 --> 01:00:52.393
Be back in 20 minutes.

1402
01:00:52.417 --> 01:00:53.917
[chattering stops]

1403
01:00:56.292 --> 01:00:58.542
Hey. What's good here?

1404
01:00:59.042 --> 01:01:00.018
Um...

1405
01:01:00.042 --> 01:01:01.042
All the...

1406
01:01:03.458 --> 01:01:04.351
things.

1407
01:01:04.375 --> 01:01:05.434
You know what?

1408
01:01:05.458 --> 01:01:06.768
Before we eat.

1409
01:01:06.792 --> 01:01:08.809
why don't I introduce you
to some of the guys.

1410
01:01:08.833 --> 01:01:11.226
People. Some of the people.

1411
01:01:11.250 --> 01:01:14.476
Didn't mean to. uh. spring all
these folks on you at once.

1412
01:01:14.500 --> 01:01:15.559
And yet...

1413
01:01:15.583 --> 01:01:18.434
These are just some
consultants that I brought in

1414
01:01:18.458 --> 01:01:19.809
for the restructure.

1415
01:01:19.833 --> 01:01:23.934
The best guys. People. the best people.

1416
01:01:23.958 --> 01:01:26.351
They'll be weighing in on
our organizational alignment.

1417
01:01:26.375 --> 01:01:29.476
operational strategy.
financial architecture.

1418
01:01:29.500 --> 01:01:33.958
digital transformation.
user experience. everything.

1419
01:01:34.583 --> 01:01:35.643
Everything.

1420
01:01:35.667 --> 01:01:37.559
Sandeep. you wanna fill Ms. Priestly in

1421
01:01:37.583 --> 01:01:38.809
on our concepts?

1422
01:01:38.833 --> 01:01:42.125
Absolutely. Sandeep Kapoor.
Harvard MBA. Not important.

1423
01:01:42.667 --> 01:01:45.518
You know. at our offices.
we call you "Miranda Beastly"

1424
01:01:45.542 --> 01:01:46.902
'cause you're a beast in the game.

1425
01:01:47.500 --> 01:01:49.393
And unfortunately. right now
what's happening is

1426
01:01:49.417 --> 01:01:50.809
that beast is leashed.

1427
01:01:50.833 --> 01:01:54.125
And we need to let that
beast free. Let it roam.

1428
01:01:54.792 --> 01:01:56.750
Ugh. Undertakers.

1429
01:01:57.667 --> 01:02:00.268
No. what? Management consultants.

1430
01:02:00.292 --> 01:02:01.434
Like I said.

1431
01:02:01.458 --> 01:02:02.851
[Nigel] McKinsey to my eye.

1432
01:02:02.875 --> 01:02:04.417
[Andy] Pfft. Cute.

1433
01:02:05.417 --> 01:02:07.059
[whispers] Wish I could hear
what they were saying.

1434
01:02:07.083 --> 01:02:08.351
- I know.
- [Andy sighs]

1435
01:02:08.375 --> 01:02:09.625
Anyone want Froyo?

1436
01:02:10.667 --> 01:02:13.000
- What?
- What? Best thing here.

1437
01:02:13.792 --> 01:02:15.292
[♪ Suspenseful music playing]

1438
01:02:17.667 --> 01:02:19.893
I worry about this generation of kids.

1439
01:02:19.917 --> 01:02:21.750
It's a national emergency.

1440
01:02:27.000 --> 01:02:29.059
It went on for an hour.

1441
01:02:29.083 --> 01:02:32.226
Miranda in the middle
of that circle of suits.

1442
01:02:32.250 --> 01:02:33.893
I have no idea what was agreed to.

1443
01:02:33.917 --> 01:02:35.018
They're gonna cut Features first.

1444
01:02:35.042 --> 01:02:36.226
They always cut the writing first.

1445
01:02:36.250 --> 01:02:38.226
Look. look... [sighs]

1446
01:02:38.250 --> 01:02:40.559
Miranda is resourceful. all right?

1447
01:02:40.583 --> 01:02:42.518
Whatever this new situation
is. she'll find a way.

1448
01:02:42.542 --> 01:02:44.393
Trust me. [scoffing]
She is always ten steps ahead.

1449
01:02:44.417 --> 01:02:45.768
Well. it's just. you know.
this whole thing

1450
01:02:45.792 --> 01:02:47.018
of having an actual job.

1451
01:02:47.042 --> 01:02:50.143
it's been. like. great. you know?

1452
01:02:50.167 --> 01:02:51.643
Yeah. I know.

1453
01:02:51.667 --> 01:02:52.643
- Hi. hi.
- [coworker] Oh. boy.

1454
01:02:52.667 --> 01:02:53.809
I need to talk to you right now.

1455
01:02:53.833 --> 01:02:56.018
Okay. Okay. Excuse me. please. What?

1456
01:02:56.042 --> 01:02:57.143
Okay.

1457
01:02:57.167 --> 01:02:58.934
You know you said
that you wanted to know about

1458
01:02:58.958 --> 01:03:00.226
what Miranda and Jay were talking about

1459
01:03:00.250 --> 01:03:01.184
in the cafeteria.

1460
01:03:01.208 --> 01:03:02.268
Yeah.

1461
01:03:02.292 --> 01:03:03.375
So...

1462
01:03:03.917 --> 01:03:04.809
What is that?

1463
01:03:04.833 --> 01:03:06.018
When I was getting Froyo.

1464
01:03:06.042 --> 01:03:07.393
I dropped my spoon on the floor.

1465
01:03:07.417 --> 01:03:08.684
and I put my phone under her chair.

1466
01:03:08.708 --> 01:03:12.059
and it was recording the whole time.

1467
01:03:12.083 --> 01:03:13.333
[♪ Mischievous music playing]

1468
01:03:13.875 --> 01:03:14.976
Jin!

1469
01:03:15.000 --> 01:03:18.809
- Yeah. Yup. yup. yup. yup.
- What? You are such a badass!

1470
01:03:18.833 --> 01:03:19.917
Yeah. I know.

1471
01:03:21.083 --> 01:03:22.309
[Jay] <i>We took a look at your budget</i>

1472
01:03:22.333 --> 01:03:25.601
<i>and have some immediate
ideas for scale-downs.</i>

1473
01:03:25.625 --> 01:03:28.684
<i>Show the markets that we are
ready to crank that EBITDA.</i>

1474
01:03:28.708 --> 01:03:30.083
I'm just gonna...

1475
01:03:32.125 --> 01:03:33.768
[exhales deeply]

1476
01:03:33.792 --> 01:03:35.226
You don't wanna know.

1477
01:03:35.250 --> 01:03:37.101
Then don't tell me.

1478
01:03:37.125 --> 01:03:38.917
Oh... Oh.

1479
01:03:40.333 --> 01:03:44.101
I was kidding. What is it? Spill it.

1480
01:03:44.125 --> 01:03:47.750
[whispering] Nigel.
they're cutting everything.

1481
01:03:48.750 --> 01:03:51.434
Features? Reduced to nothing.

1482
01:03:51.458 --> 01:03:53.018
Fashion and Beauty? Decimated.

1483
01:03:53.042 --> 01:03:54.643
Cuts across all departments.

1484
01:03:54.667 --> 01:03:56.726
and anyone who's been here
for longer than five years

1485
01:03:56.750 --> 01:03:58.393
is too expensive and has to go.

1486
01:03:58.417 --> 01:03:59.417
I'm sorry.

1487
01:04:00.833 --> 01:04:02.101
That makes sense.

1488
01:04:02.125 --> 01:04:04.018
- And you know what she said?
- [Nigel] Nope.

1489
01:04:04.042 --> 01:04:05.833
Not a single thing.

1490
01:04:08.000 --> 01:04:09.000
Nigel.

1491
01:04:13.375 --> 01:04:14.583
You know what I think?

1492
01:04:15.667 --> 01:04:20.792
I think I like the bag cross-body.

1493
01:04:24.292 --> 01:04:25.583
That's what I think.

1494
01:04:28.125 --> 01:04:29.125
All right.

1495
01:04:29.792 --> 01:04:31.000
I'll leave you to it.

1496
01:04:40.292 --> 01:04:42.643
[The Marias “No One Noticed” playing]

1497
01:04:42.667 --> 01:04:44.934
I just can't believe
this is happening again.

1498
01:04:44.958 --> 01:04:46.958
Another publication. deleted.

1499
01:04:48.875 --> 01:04:51.833
- I'm sorry. Andy. It sucks.
- Sucks.

1500
01:04:56.042 --> 01:04:58.042
This is where it's all going.
you know? It's...

1501
01:04:58.542 --> 01:04:59.476
It's happening all over.

1502
01:04:59.500 --> 01:05:00.893
It's pharmacies. it's bookstores.

1503
01:05:00.917 --> 01:05:01.809
It's... You name it.

1504
01:05:01.833 --> 01:05:04.393
It's all being downsized.
It's all consolidating.

1505
01:05:04.417 --> 01:05:06.309
No. I just can't accept that. I...

1506
01:05:06.333 --> 01:05:09.101
We... We can't just keep

1507
01:05:09.125 --> 01:05:11.309
sucking the soul out of everything.

1508
01:05:11.333 --> 01:05:14.184
And-and gutting it
and then repackaging it.

1509
01:05:14.208 --> 01:05:15.708
To what end?

1510
01:05:16.250 --> 01:05:19.143
But it's... it's...
We're replacing it. you know?

1511
01:05:19.167 --> 01:05:20.643
I mean. you've basically just described

1512
01:05:20.667 --> 01:05:22.027
what I've done with this building.

1513
01:05:22.667 --> 01:05:25.434
Peter. we're not talking about
you right now. We're talk...

1514
01:05:25.458 --> 01:05:26.643
And also. like.

1515
01:05:26.667 --> 01:05:30.750
journalism matters
more than luxury apartments.

1516
01:05:32.833 --> 01:05:33.917
That's true.

1517
01:05:35.958 --> 01:05:37.625
I'm sorry. I'm just...

1518
01:05:38.250 --> 01:05:40.601
This is such a spectacularly
helpful conversation.

1519
01:05:40.625 --> 01:05:41.518
Thank you.

1520
01:05:41.542 --> 01:05:43.083
- Is it not?
- No.

1521
01:05:49.250 --> 01:05:51.143
I might give you a minute.

1522
01:05:51.167 --> 01:05:52.292
Thanks.

1523
01:05:58.292 --> 01:06:00.601
Hey. I. uh...
I know you gotta go to Italy.

1524
01:06:00.625 --> 01:06:02.250
but if you wanna... [sighs]

1525
01:06:03.208 --> 01:06:05.368
If you wanna catch up
when you're back. I'd like it.

1526
01:06:06.292 --> 01:06:07.583
But it's up to you.

1527
01:06:11.792 --> 01:06:12.792
[door closes]

1528
01:06:13.458 --> 01:06:15.958
- [horns honking]
- [dogs barking in distance]

1529
01:06:31.917 --> 01:06:32.917
[doorbell chimes]

1530
01:06:34.250 --> 01:06:35.333
Hmm. no.

1531
01:06:36.667 --> 01:06:38.643
- Oh. hi. Stuart.
- Andy.

1532
01:06:38.667 --> 01:06:40.018
- Yes.
- You all right?

1533
01:06:40.042 --> 01:06:42.476
- [stammers] Could I come in?
- Sure. absolutely.

1534
01:06:42.500 --> 01:06:44.518
Um. wasn't expecting you. I suppose.

1535
01:06:44.542 --> 01:06:49.268
Sorry to bother you.
I just. um. need. uh...

1536
01:06:49.292 --> 01:06:51.101
- I think... [inhales deeply]
- Catch your breath maybe.

1537
01:06:51.125 --> 01:06:53.792
Okay. Can't. Um. is she here?

1538
01:06:54.292 --> 01:06:56.167
Yeah. she's. um...

1539
01:07:03.250 --> 01:07:04.417
Brave.

1540
01:07:07.083 --> 01:07:08.083
Ah.

1541
01:07:08.917 --> 01:07:11.042
I don't mean to bother you.
I just need to talk.

1542
01:07:12.167 --> 01:07:14.143
- Talk.
- So. uh. I just need to...

1543
01:07:14.167 --> 01:07:16.393
I just need to... You have a plan. right?

1544
01:07:16.417 --> 01:07:18.018
A secret plan like...

1545
01:07:18.042 --> 01:07:19.518
- like you did...
- I can't hear you.

1546
01:07:19.542 --> 01:07:21.434
Don't you have people you can call?

1547
01:07:21.458 --> 01:07:23.934
I just don't want everyone
to lose their jobs.

1548
01:07:23.958 --> 01:07:24.851
Please. Miranda.

1549
01:07:24.875 --> 01:07:26.768
we have been doing such great work lately.

1550
01:07:26.792 --> 01:07:28.476
We're attracting great writers.

1551
01:07:28.500 --> 01:07:31.018
and people care about the magazine again.

1552
01:07:31.042 --> 01:07:33.434
This job has let me hope again

1553
01:07:33.458 --> 01:07:35.184
for the future. for our future. my future.

1554
01:07:35.208 --> 01:07:37.101
I... I might be able to unfreeze an egg.

1555
01:07:37.125 --> 01:07:38.309
Go home.

1556
01:07:38.333 --> 01:07:40.226
- But I...
- It's late.

1557
01:07:40.250 --> 01:07:43.250
Do not concern yourself with this.

1558
01:07:45.583 --> 01:07:48.125
[quietly] It does not concern you.

1559
01:07:54.083 --> 01:07:56.083
[♪ Somber music playing]

1560
01:08:01.042 --> 01:08:02.708
[sighs]

1561
01:08:11.917 --> 01:08:14.375
Hmm. Huh.

1562
01:08:19.458 --> 01:08:20.458
[sighs]

1563
01:08:25.583 --> 01:08:27.583
[keyboard clicking]

1564
01:08:32.500 --> 01:08:34.351
<i>Allora. Milano...</i>

1565
01:08:34.375 --> 01:08:36.726
Nigel. you were saying
that some new directives

1566
01:08:36.750 --> 01:08:38.833
have come in from on high.

1567
01:08:39.875 --> 01:08:41.226
Budget cuts?

1568
01:08:41.250 --> 01:08:44.184
Yes. so. regarding Milan.

1569
01:08:44.208 --> 01:08:46.559
we're cutting John Legend

1570
01:08:46.583 --> 01:08:48.643
because he wants us to ship
his piano there.

1571
01:08:48.667 --> 01:08:49.893
and that's too pricey.

1572
01:08:49.917 --> 01:08:51.542
So. no music.

1573
01:08:52.542 --> 01:08:53.934
Unless we call in a favor.

1574
01:08:53.958 --> 01:08:54.958
[pen clicks]

1575
01:08:56.625 --> 01:08:57.667
No.

1576
01:09:01.917 --> 01:09:04.059
No. She's impossible.

1577
01:09:04.083 --> 01:09:05.583
That cover almost...

1578
01:09:07.042 --> 01:09:07.934
killed me.

1579
01:09:07.958 --> 01:09:13.143
Fine. No music. None at all. No music.

1580
01:09:13.167 --> 01:09:15.143
- Okay. fine. I'll call her.
- Thank you.

1581
01:09:15.167 --> 01:09:19.059
Now. there are a few new
policies across the board.

1582
01:09:19.083 --> 01:09:23.476
The first one is no more
private cars. Uber only.

1583
01:09:23.500 --> 01:09:24.393
[gasps]

1584
01:09:24.417 --> 01:09:27.417
And as for the flights...

1585
01:09:30.292 --> 01:09:31.809
<i>Good afternoon. ladies and gentlemen.</i>

1586
01:09:31.833 --> 01:09:34.559
<i>and welcome aboard
United Airlines Flight 19</i>

1587
01:09:34.583 --> 01:09:36.559
<i>with service to Milan. Italy.</i>

1588
01:09:36.583 --> 01:09:38.226
<i>We'll be coming by with champagne</i>

1589
01:09:38.250 --> 01:09:40.934
<i>for our Polaris business
class passengers shortly.</i>

1590
01:09:40.958 --> 01:09:43.976
<i>If you're seated in economy.
we do have a full flight today</i>

1591
01:09:44.000 --> 01:09:46.601
<i>so please stow your carry-ons
in the overhead compartments</i>

1592
01:09:46.625 --> 01:09:49.434
<i>above you and secure any
personal bags or belongings</i>

1593
01:09:49.458 --> 01:09:51.042
<i>under the seat in front of you.</i>

1594
01:09:51.542 --> 01:09:54.042
I need some... Get me something to drink.

1595
01:10:01.125 --> 01:10:02.726
What is wrong with Miranda?

1596
01:10:02.750 --> 01:10:04.292
Why is she putting up with this?

1597
01:10:04.917 --> 01:10:06.809
Excuse me. Excuse me.

1598
01:10:06.833 --> 01:10:08.434
Uh. Ms. Priestly would like a glass

1599
01:10:08.458 --> 01:10:09.684
of your finest champagne.

1600
01:10:09.708 --> 01:10:12.000
I'm sorry. That's not served
in this cabin.

1601
01:10:12.583 --> 01:10:14.125
They have snack boxes.

1602
01:10:14.875 --> 01:10:16.476
Mmm. Um... [clears throat]

1603
01:10:16.500 --> 01:10:18.000
A snack box perhaps?

1604
01:10:20.083 --> 01:10:22.083
[♪ Madonna "Vogue" playing]

1605
01:10:24.167 --> 01:10:25.167
<i>♪ Vogue ♪</i>

1606
01:10:26.667 --> 01:10:28.726
- [people chattering]
- [photographers clamoring]

1607
01:10:28.750 --> 01:10:30.309
<i>♪ Look around ♪</i>

1608
01:10:30.333 --> 01:10:32.684
<i>♪ Everywhere you turn Is heartache ♪</i>

1609
01:10:32.708 --> 01:10:37.101
<i>♪ It's everywhere that you go
Look around ♪</i>

1610
01:10:37.125 --> 01:10:40.893
<i>♪ You try everything you can To escape ♪</i>

1611
01:10:40.917 --> 01:10:43.268
<i>♪ The pain of life That you know ♪</i>

1612
01:10:43.292 --> 01:10:44.601
<i>♪ Life that you know ♪</i>

1613
01:10:44.625 --> 01:10:48.351
<i>♪ When all else fails And you long to be ♪</i>

1614
01:10:48.375 --> 01:10:51.625
<i>♪ Something better Than you are today ♪</i>

1615
01:10:53.250 --> 01:10:56.351
<i>♪ I know a place Where you can get away ♪</i>

1616
01:10:56.375 --> 01:10:58.476
<i>♪ It's called a dance floor ♪</i>

1617
01:10:58.500 --> 01:11:00.518
<i>♪ And here's what it's for ♪</i>

1618
01:11:00.542 --> 01:11:02.976
<i>♪ So come on. vogue ♪</i>

1619
01:11:03.000 --> 01:11:04.309
<i>♪ Vogue ♪</i>

1620
01:11:04.333 --> 01:11:07.768
<i>♪ Let your body Move to the music ♪</i>

1621
01:11:07.792 --> 01:11:09.518
<i>♪ Hey. hey. hey ♪</i>

1622
01:11:09.542 --> 01:11:11.351
<i>♪ Come on. vogue ♪</i>

1623
01:11:11.375 --> 01:11:12.559
<i>♪ Vogue ♪</i>

1624
01:11:12.583 --> 01:11:15.434
<i>♪ Let your body Go with the flow ♪</i>

1625
01:11:15.458 --> 01:11:17.917
<i>♪ You know you can do it ♪</i>

1626
01:11:30.167 --> 01:11:31.833
Oh. it's so beautiful!

1627
01:11:33.208 --> 01:11:34.333
Just click it.

1628
01:11:35.958 --> 01:11:38.268
- [Benji] Look at that.
- [Emily] What do you think?

1629
01:11:38.292 --> 01:11:42.434
- Oh. yeah. Uh-huh.
- What do you think. Benji?

1630
01:11:42.458 --> 01:11:43.684
[sighs]

1631
01:11:43.708 --> 01:11:45.059
What are you doing?

1632
01:11:45.083 --> 01:11:47.476
Uh... [chuckles] Got hypnotized.

1633
01:11:47.500 --> 01:11:49.393
Benji's buying Emily a very nice necklace.

1634
01:11:49.417 --> 01:11:51.643
Yes. I'm not surprised.

1635
01:11:51.667 --> 01:11:53.583
Last week. he bought her a Monet.

1636
01:11:54.792 --> 01:11:55.768
And a Klimt.

1637
01:11:55.792 --> 01:11:57.667
- Really?
- Oh. yes.

1638
01:11:59.125 --> 01:12:00.018
Come on.

1639
01:12:00.042 --> 01:12:01.684
- What?
- No. I mean. we're gonna...

1640
01:12:01.708 --> 01:12:03.976
Hey. just put it on my tab
here. Just put it on my tab.

1641
01:12:04.000 --> 01:12:05.643
Ah. <i>Pronto</i>?

1642
01:12:05.667 --> 01:12:08.643
<i>Pronto. sì. pronto.</i> Um...

1643
01:12:08.667 --> 01:12:12.208
<i>Posso avere il numero di camera...</i>

1644
01:12:13.458 --> 01:12:15.143
Yes. I need a room number.

1645
01:12:15.167 --> 01:12:17.393
<i>Mommy. Roark said he wants</i>

1646
01:12:17.417 --> 01:12:19.018
<i>the éclair from Miss Madeleine.</i>

1647
01:12:19.042 --> 01:12:21.018
<i>but it was my idea to go there.</i>

1648
01:12:21.042 --> 01:12:23.393
Oh. bunny. what do we do
when we get a bit wobbly?

1649
01:12:23.417 --> 01:12:24.434
We... That's right.

1650
01:12:24.458 --> 01:12:26.809
- Breathe in. hold...
- [Bronwyn] <i>Breathe in. hold.</i>

1651
01:12:26.833 --> 01:12:27.726
[inhales deeply]

1652
01:12:27.750 --> 01:12:28.809
And breathe out.

1653
01:12:28.833 --> 01:12:29.976
And don't forget to do the tappy-tap.

1654
01:12:30.000 --> 01:12:31.684
tappy-tap it all away.

1655
01:12:31.708 --> 01:12:33.768
- There we are. Is that better?
- [Bronwyn] <i>Uh-huh.</i>

1656
01:12:33.792 --> 01:12:35.934
Okay. my love. Now. listen.
can you go get Daddy?

1657
01:12:35.958 --> 01:12:37.768
All right. Love ya.

1658
01:12:37.792 --> 01:12:39.434
<i>- What's up?</i>
- Frank.

1659
01:12:39.458 --> 01:12:41.434
I am in Milan. and as you can see.

1660
01:12:41.458 --> 01:12:43.434
I am stretched thinner
than a pair of Spanx.

1661
01:12:43.458 --> 01:12:45.643
so can you just try parenting?

1662
01:12:45.667 --> 01:12:46.684
Go to Miss Madeleine

1663
01:12:46.708 --> 01:12:47.768
and get them the bloody éclair.

1664
01:12:47.792 --> 01:12:49.184
- I can't do everything.
<i>- You went to Italy.</i>

1665
01:12:49.208 --> 01:12:50.500
<i>I'm here. So...</i>

1666
01:12:59.417 --> 01:13:02.226
[exhales]

1667
01:13:02.250 --> 01:13:06.000
May the bridges I burn light my way.

1668
01:13:06.625 --> 01:13:08.417
- [knocking on door]
- God.

1669
01:13:15.833 --> 01:13:16.976
Hi.

1670
01:13:17.000 --> 01:13:18.434
- [Emily] Andy.
- Do you have a sec?

1671
01:13:18.458 --> 01:13:20.208
- Yes.
- Okay.

1672
01:13:22.250 --> 01:13:23.250
[elevator bell dings]

1673
01:13:25.083 --> 01:13:27.083
[♪ Adventurous music playing]

1674
01:13:28.208 --> 01:13:29.351
Okay.

1675
01:13:29.375 --> 01:13:30.851
Well. hello.

1676
01:13:30.875 --> 01:13:33.518
- Hi. [chuckles]
- Look at us. up before dawn.

1677
01:13:33.542 --> 01:13:35.101
I just went for a stroll.
What are you doing?

1678
01:13:35.125 --> 01:13:37.101
- Me? Um...
- Yeah. Where are you going?

1679
01:13:37.125 --> 01:13:38.518
- Como.
- Ah.

1680
01:13:38.542 --> 01:13:40.143
Yeah. I'm doing that story on the winery.

1681
01:13:40.167 --> 01:13:41.726
Oh. Right. right.

1682
01:13:41.750 --> 01:13:42.726
That's cute.

1683
01:13:42.750 --> 01:13:43.809
Dinner tonight?

1684
01:13:43.833 --> 01:13:45.768
I always eat with Tom Ford at Da Giacomo.

1685
01:13:45.792 --> 01:13:47.434
- Little gossip sesh? Hmm?
- Uh-huh. Um.

1686
01:13:47.458 --> 01:13:48.726
Okay. great. I'll text you.

1687
01:13:48.750 --> 01:13:49.750
- Okay.
- Okay.

1688
01:13:53.167 --> 01:13:54.167
Hmm.

1689
01:13:55.667 --> 01:13:56.559
[Emily] Come on.

1690
01:13:56.583 --> 01:13:58.309
Window up. Window up.
Nigel's watching. Nigel.

1691
01:13:58.333 --> 01:14:00.167
What? Bloody hell.

1692
01:14:35.208 --> 01:14:37.042
[laughs]

1693
01:14:37.708 --> 01:14:38.934
There she is.

1694
01:14:38.958 --> 01:14:41.893
Oh. hi. honey. Hi. Don't.

1695
01:14:41.917 --> 01:14:43.708
I'm sorry. I'm just saying. "hello."

1696
01:14:47.875 --> 01:14:49.417
So how long have you had a place here?

1697
01:14:50.750 --> 01:14:51.934
- Me?
- Mm-hmm.

1698
01:14:51.958 --> 01:14:53.684
- Oh. God. Um...
- [in Italian] <i>Grazie.</i>

1699
01:14:53.708 --> 01:14:54.851
[laughs]

1700
01:14:54.875 --> 01:14:56.059
[in English] I don't know. I don't know.

1701
01:14:56.083 --> 01:14:57.684
He doesn't remember anything.

1702
01:14:57.708 --> 01:14:59.018
- Nothing.
- [chuckles]

1703
01:14:59.042 --> 01:14:59.934
Oh. no. no.

1704
01:14:59.958 --> 01:15:01.351
[in Italian] <i>Non. non per mio. grazie.</i>

1705
01:15:01.375 --> 01:15:03.226
- No. thank you. Massimo.
- [in Italian] <i>Ciao.</i>

1706
01:15:03.250 --> 01:15:04.184
[in English] Not having anything?

1707
01:15:04.208 --> 01:15:06.309
No. I'm not doing water these days.

1708
01:15:06.333 --> 01:15:08.101
Trying to operate at an aqua deficit.

1709
01:15:08.125 --> 01:15:09.684
- It's poison.
- [Emily] Not poison.

1710
01:15:09.708 --> 01:15:11.292
- [Benji] It is poison.
- So. uh.

1711
01:15:12.417 --> 01:15:13.768
do you think we can pull this off?

1712
01:15:13.792 --> 01:15:14.851
[Benji] Depends on what he's asking.

1713
01:15:14.875 --> 01:15:16.268
- Oh. come on. BB.
- What?

1714
01:15:16.292 --> 01:15:18.018
You can persuade anyone
of anything. You know that.

1715
01:15:18.042 --> 01:15:18.934
Well. that's true.

1716
01:15:18.958 --> 01:15:20.518
I did persuade this one
to go on a date with me.

1717
01:15:20.542 --> 01:15:21.809
To go on a date with you.

1718
01:15:21.833 --> 01:15:22.833
- I know.
- [laughs]

1719
01:15:23.625 --> 01:15:25.309
With all of that ear hair.

1720
01:15:25.333 --> 01:15:27.393
Oh my... Oh. please.

1721
01:15:27.417 --> 01:15:28.601
It was so awful.

1722
01:15:28.625 --> 01:15:30.309
Andy. if you had seen me
before I met this one.

1723
01:15:30.333 --> 01:15:31.393
I had ear hair.

1724
01:15:31.417 --> 01:15:32.559
[Emily] It was like a jungle in there.

1725
01:15:32.583 --> 01:15:33.559
So much hair growing out of them.

1726
01:15:33.583 --> 01:15:34.643
I had to get him one of the things.

1727
01:15:34.667 --> 01:15:36.518
- The buzzy thing.
- The buzzer. [imitates buzzer]

1728
01:15:36.542 --> 01:15:38.583
Yeah. and then a lawn mower for the rest.

1729
01:15:39.417 --> 01:15:41.684
Can you imagine lawn-mowing my chest?

1730
01:15:41.708 --> 01:15:44.458
I know. I just like him
like a bar of soap.

1731
01:15:45.083 --> 01:15:46.809
That's right. just hairless.

1732
01:15:46.833 --> 01:15:47.893
- [Emily] Oh. there he is.
- Oh.

1733
01:15:47.917 --> 01:15:49.476
What we need to do is get four people on.

1734
01:15:49.500 --> 01:15:50.559
We need to get the accountant.

1735
01:15:50.583 --> 01:15:51.726
we need to get the business manager.

1736
01:15:51.750 --> 01:15:53.018
We need to get everybody's team.

1737
01:15:53.042 --> 01:15:54.726
- Everybody's team.
- Jay!

1738
01:15:54.750 --> 01:15:55.893
Real quick. then.

1739
01:15:55.917 --> 01:15:57.476
You wanna tell me quick?
You can tell me quick.

1740
01:15:57.500 --> 01:15:58.393
[Benji] Jay-Jay!

1741
01:15:58.417 --> 01:15:59.643
You wanna tell me slow.
you can tell me slow.

1742
01:15:59.667 --> 01:16:01.643
- Does he not see us?
- Not at all.

1743
01:16:01.667 --> 01:16:03.667
[bell tolling]

1744
01:16:09.917 --> 01:16:10.976
Oh. there you are.

1745
01:16:11.000 --> 01:16:12.393
- Oh. hi.
- Hi.

1746
01:16:12.417 --> 01:16:13.601
Hey. how was your dinner?

1747
01:16:13.625 --> 01:16:15.393
- Lovely. How was yours?
- Mmm.

1748
01:16:15.417 --> 01:16:17.018
Oh. you know. I just ordered room service.

1749
01:16:17.042 --> 01:16:18.143
- Oh. yeah? Yeah.
- Mm-hmm.

1750
01:16:18.167 --> 01:16:19.893
I love their <i>baccalà mantecato</i> here.

1751
01:16:19.917 --> 01:16:21.434
- Yum. It was so good.
- Yeah.

1752
01:16:21.458 --> 01:16:22.768
Yeah. they don't have that here.

1753
01:16:22.792 --> 01:16:24.809
That's a Venetian dish. not <i>milanese</i>.

1754
01:16:24.833 --> 01:16:26.143
- I...
- Tell me the truth.

1755
01:16:26.167 --> 01:16:27.809
- What's going on?
- What? Nigel.

1756
01:16:27.833 --> 01:16:28.893
You're skulking.

1757
01:16:28.917 --> 01:16:31.059
I know a skulk when I see a skulk.

1758
01:16:31.083 --> 01:16:32.726
- Tell me.
- And... She's here.

1759
01:16:32.750 --> 01:16:36.000
- Morning.
- I can't do this clasp.

1760
01:16:36.500 --> 01:16:37.500
Ready?

1761
01:16:40.958 --> 01:16:43.976
[Nigel] Obviously. security
is going to be very intense.

1762
01:16:44.000 --> 01:16:49.917
And we have hired extensive
<i>protezione</i> for the art.

1763
01:16:53.917 --> 01:16:55.059
[in Italian] <i>Grazie.</i>

1764
01:16:55.083 --> 01:16:56.143
[in English] Okay. everybody.

1765
01:16:56.167 --> 01:17:00.458
I'd like to run through
the dinner for the clients.

1766
01:17:01.167 --> 01:17:02.434
the seating.

1767
01:17:02.458 --> 01:17:04.934
so we have a U-shaped table.

1768
01:17:04.958 --> 01:17:06.500
That's the head up there.

1769
01:17:07.208 --> 01:17:09.559
It's going to end around here someplace.

1770
01:17:09.583 --> 01:17:11.167
about 40 people or more...

1771
01:17:11.875 --> 01:17:13.476
And we're going to take the brands.

1772
01:17:13.500 --> 01:17:15.059
and we're going to mix them up...

1773
01:17:15.083 --> 01:17:16.976
Do you know much about <i>The Last Supper</i>?

1774
01:17:17.000 --> 01:17:18.059
[stammers]

1775
01:17:18.083 --> 01:17:19.333
Not as much as I should.

1776
01:17:20.333 --> 01:17:23.958
Painting this particular scene
was nothing new.

1777
01:17:25.208 --> 01:17:28.351
You can find frescoes
of the same subject matter

1778
01:17:28.375 --> 01:17:29.268
all over Europe.

1779
01:17:29.292 --> 01:17:32.893
but in the other versions.

1780
01:17:32.917 --> 01:17:36.250
the man in charge is
usually depicted with a halo.

1781
01:17:39.292 --> 01:17:43.393
People think that it was
da Vinci's way of saying.

1782
01:17:43.417 --> 01:17:46.417
"We are human. No one is perfect."

1783
01:17:47.708 --> 01:17:52.250
Humans are at once glorious and fallible.

1784
01:17:53.375 --> 01:17:57.309
And inevitably we deceive
and betray one another.

1785
01:17:57.333 --> 01:17:59.250
let each other down.

1786
01:18:00.000 --> 01:18:02.226
[sighs]

1787
01:18:02.250 --> 01:18:04.542
It's what we're built to do.

1788
01:18:08.708 --> 01:18:09.708
Would you agree?

1789
01:18:18.625 --> 01:18:20.625
[♪ Tense music plays]

1790
01:18:28.042 --> 01:18:29.333
Okay. Yes.

1791
01:18:41.500 --> 01:18:42.726
[laughs]

1792
01:18:42.750 --> 01:18:45.083
What's Andy doing beetling around here?

1793
01:18:45.625 --> 01:18:46.625
[in Italian] <i>Scusa.</i>

1794
01:18:48.208 --> 01:18:49.726
- [in English] Can I help you?
- Miranda knows.

1795
01:18:49.750 --> 01:18:51.018
- What do you mean she knows?
- She knows.

1796
01:18:51.042 --> 01:18:53.268
- How? Did you blab?
- No. but I don't...

1797
01:18:53.292 --> 01:18:54.601
She made it terrifyingly clear to me

1798
01:18:54.625 --> 01:18:55.851
she is aware something is up.

1799
01:18:55.875 --> 01:18:57.101
Oh. for God's sake.

1800
01:18:57.125 --> 01:18:58.684
And I know that we're just
doing this to help her

1801
01:18:58.708 --> 01:19:00.143
but I honestly can't
with the secrets anymore.

1802
01:19:00.167 --> 01:19:01.559
so I think we just...
like. we should tell her.

1803
01:19:01.583 --> 01:19:02.643
- No...
- Yes.

1804
01:19:02.667 --> 01:19:04.476
We will wait until it is done. please.

1805
01:19:04.500 --> 01:19:06.143
[in Italian] Emily. <i>dai</i>

1806
01:19:06.167 --> 01:19:07.143
<i>Mi dai un momento?</i>

1807
01:19:07.167 --> 01:19:08.851
<i>Perché sei sempre
così impaziente. Donatella?</i>

1808
01:19:08.875 --> 01:19:09.976
<i>Per favore!</i>

1809
01:19:10.000 --> 01:19:11.040
[in English] Emily. focus.

1810
01:19:12.125 --> 01:19:13.184
We need to tell Miranda.

1811
01:19:13.208 --> 01:19:14.500
We need to tell her now.

1812
01:19:15.333 --> 01:19:17.000
I feel a little bit sick.

1813
01:19:19.167 --> 01:19:20.393
I'm so nervous I can't breathe.

1814
01:19:20.417 --> 01:19:22.268
- [pants] My neck is hot.
- Oh. my God.

1815
01:19:22.292 --> 01:19:24.643
Just hide a feeling for once. please.

1816
01:19:24.667 --> 01:19:25.917
[knocking on door]

1817
01:19:28.083 --> 01:19:29.083
Oh.

1818
01:19:29.625 --> 01:19:30.559
The Emilys.

1819
01:19:30.583 --> 01:19:32.184
I thought you were Amari.

1820
01:19:32.208 --> 01:19:34.476
Waiting for my Armani.

1821
01:19:34.500 --> 01:19:36.292
Has she been human trafficked?

1822
01:19:36.958 --> 01:19:40.042
Oh. Uh. Jay sprung for the big suite.

1823
01:19:40.667 --> 01:19:41.601
Yeah.

1824
01:19:41.625 --> 01:19:44.893
Well. it's a little snug.
but. you know. I'll manage.

1825
01:19:44.917 --> 01:19:46.393
How can I help you two?

1826
01:19:46.417 --> 01:19:47.417
Um...

1827
01:19:47.917 --> 01:19:50.434
- Okay. Miranda.
- Mm-hmm.

1828
01:19:50.458 --> 01:19:52.601
What Jay wants to do with <i>Runway.</i>

1829
01:19:52.625 --> 01:19:53.851
scaling it so far back that it

1830
01:19:53.875 --> 01:19:56.018
doesn't even resemble what it used to be.

1831
01:19:56.042 --> 01:19:57.434
cutting my department.

1832
01:19:57.458 --> 01:19:59.184
Nigel and most of his department...

1833
01:19:59.208 --> 01:20:00.559
How do you know about that?

1834
01:20:00.583 --> 01:20:03.893
Look. we all know how important

1835
01:20:03.917 --> 01:20:05.434
<i>Runway</i> is and has been.

1836
01:20:05.458 --> 01:20:07.601
Yeah. I mean. <i>Runway</i> is
practically a religion

1837
01:20:07.625 --> 01:20:09.726
and it needs to be protected.

1838
01:20:09.750 --> 01:20:11.476
So I think. you know. the question is.

1839
01:20:11.500 --> 01:20:13.393
who has the means to acquire it?

1840
01:20:13.417 --> 01:20:15.143
Will you two please spit it out already?

1841
01:20:15.167 --> 01:20:16.226
Um... [stammers]

1842
01:20:16.250 --> 01:20:17.309
Benji's buying <i>Runway</i>.

1843
01:20:17.333 --> 01:20:19.768
Benji? Benji Barnes?

1844
01:20:19.792 --> 01:20:22.393
My Benji made Jay Ravitz an offer.

1845
01:20:22.417 --> 01:20:25.208
and Jay readily accepted.

1846
01:20:25.917 --> 01:20:27.434
And you had a part in this?

1847
01:20:27.458 --> 01:20:30.476
Yes. we're doing it
to protect <i>Runway</i> and you.

1848
01:20:30.500 --> 01:20:33.309
You'll be editor-in-chief
for as long as you want to be.

1849
01:20:33.333 --> 01:20:35.101
[stammers] I'm sorry.

1850
01:20:35.125 --> 01:20:38.976
I... I know we've had our differences.

1851
01:20:39.000 --> 01:20:40.167
but I just... I...

1852
01:20:41.542 --> 01:20:43.184
Well. now. I never realized that you

1853
01:20:43.208 --> 01:20:45.018
were capable of this level of betrayal.

1854
01:20:45.042 --> 01:20:46.851
Betrayal? No. Miranda.

1855
01:20:46.875 --> 01:20:49.083
we're preserving <i>Runway</i> for you.

1856
01:20:49.667 --> 01:20:50.559
[Miranda] Oh. no. no. no.

1857
01:20:50.583 --> 01:20:53.750
Miss Emily is not preserving
anything for anybody.

1858
01:20:54.625 --> 01:20:55.851
[stammers] Yes. she is.

1859
01:20:55.875 --> 01:20:56.934
[chuckles] Yes. of course she is.

1860
01:20:56.958 --> 01:20:58.000
Emily.

1861
01:21:00.792 --> 01:21:03.018
Emily. tell her.

1862
01:21:03.042 --> 01:21:04.583
Yeah. Emily.

1863
01:21:05.458 --> 01:21:06.625
Tell her.

1864
01:21:14.083 --> 01:21:15.542
Well. she's right. [sighs]

1865
01:21:18.625 --> 01:21:20.625
Benji's buying <i>Runway</i> for me.

1866
01:21:22.375 --> 01:21:23.684
So that I can run it.

1867
01:21:23.708 --> 01:21:25.348
- What are you talking about?
- [chuckles]

1868
01:21:26.250 --> 01:21:27.434
Look. she's had a long run.

1869
01:21:27.458 --> 01:21:28.833
A historic run.

1870
01:21:29.750 --> 01:21:30.833
But she's exhausted.

1871
01:21:31.500 --> 01:21:35.000
And... And I'm fresher and younger.

1872
01:21:36.458 --> 01:21:38.643
I want to set tastes.
not just cater to them.

1873
01:21:38.667 --> 01:21:40.143
Why would... Why would you do this?

1874
01:21:40.167 --> 01:21:41.726
She knows why.

1875
01:21:41.750 --> 01:21:43.851
[stammers] I have no idea.

1876
01:21:43.875 --> 01:21:45.893
You pushed me out. didn't you?

1877
01:21:45.917 --> 01:21:47.351
I did nothing of the kind.

1878
01:21:47.375 --> 01:21:50.833
You made Dior hire me to get rid of me.

1879
01:21:51.375 --> 01:21:53.458
Why? Why did... Why did you do that?

1880
01:21:54.417 --> 01:21:55.768
[smacks lips. sighs]

1881
01:21:55.792 --> 01:21:57.018
For the same reason

1882
01:21:57.042 --> 01:22:00.184
that you should never
be in charge of <i>Runway.</i> Emily.

1883
01:22:00.208 --> 01:22:03.309
because you are beautiful
and you're intelligent.

1884
01:22:03.333 --> 01:22:04.542
but. no...

1885
01:22:06.333 --> 01:22:08.292
you don't have what it takes.

1886
01:22:09.833 --> 01:22:13.208
I'm sorry. but you're not a visionary.

1887
01:22:15.458 --> 01:22:16.750
You're a vendor.

1888
01:22:18.208 --> 01:22:19.917
You don't know that.

1889
01:22:22.375 --> 01:22:23.851
You don't know the first thing about me.

1890
01:22:23.875 --> 01:22:25.268
You never cared to...

1891
01:22:25.292 --> 01:22:29.417
Oh. I think I do.
and I also think. deep down...

1892
01:22:30.750 --> 01:22:31.750
you know I'm right.

1893
01:22:36.250 --> 01:22:37.250
That's all.

1894
01:22:39.083 --> 01:22:40.333
[breathes shakily]

1895
01:22:42.958 --> 01:22:46.458
Well. Benji's lawyers.
they will be in touch.

1896
01:22:47.333 --> 01:22:48.750
With all the details.

1897
01:22:53.792 --> 01:22:58.018
[stammers] I had no idea.
I'm... I'm so sorry.

1898
01:22:58.042 --> 01:23:00.417
I just felt I had to do something.

1899
01:23:01.708 --> 01:23:03.917
I hope that's not what
you're wearing to the dinner.

1900
01:23:05.958 --> 01:23:07.375
[stammers]

1901
01:23:16.042 --> 01:23:17.458
[sighs]

1902
01:23:20.083 --> 01:23:22.292
[bell tolling]

1903
01:23:26.083 --> 01:23:27.333
[phone buzzes]

1904
01:23:31.375 --> 01:23:33.143
Hey. What's up? How are you?

1905
01:23:33.167 --> 01:23:35.143
Oh. my God. Andy. these pages you sent...

1906
01:23:35.167 --> 01:23:36.309
My boss is freaking out.

1907
01:23:36.333 --> 01:23:37.643
These are perfect.

1908
01:23:37.667 --> 01:23:39.000
Oh. Uh...

1909
01:23:39.542 --> 01:23:41.059
So about that. um. I don't...

1910
01:23:41.083 --> 01:23:42.643
[Talia] <i>There's so much promise here.</i>

1911
01:23:42.667 --> 01:23:44.809
<i>I'm sending you an offer and a contract.</i>

1912
01:23:44.833 --> 01:23:47.559
And. Andy. it's not 50.

1913
01:23:47.583 --> 01:23:48.750
It's not 100.

1914
01:23:49.417 --> 01:23:51.184
It's 350.

1915
01:23:51.208 --> 01:23:52.917
<i>It's three-freaking-fifty.</i>

1916
01:23:56.458 --> 01:23:57.684
- No.
- [Talia] <i>No?</i>

1917
01:23:57.708 --> 01:23:58.768
What do... What do you mean. "no"?

1918
01:23:58.792 --> 01:24:00.893
Don't you mean. like. "hooray"?

1919
01:24:00.917 --> 01:24:02.309
This book.

1920
01:24:02.333 --> 01:24:05.226
it could harm Miranda. I don't...

1921
01:24:05.250 --> 01:24:08.125
[Talia] <i>Which is fine
because she's atrocious.</i>

1922
01:24:08.875 --> 01:24:10.750
It's more complicated than that.

1923
01:24:11.250 --> 01:24:15.101
Okay. Stockholm called.
They want their syndrome back.

1924
01:24:15.125 --> 01:24:18.184
I... [stammers] Can I call you back later?

1925
01:24:18.208 --> 01:24:19.559
Okay. Thanks for letting me know.

1926
01:24:19.583 --> 01:24:20.583
Bye.

1927
01:24:22.167 --> 01:24:24.184
[breathes heavily]

1928
01:24:24.208 --> 01:24:27.250
[Benji laughs] The moon? We've
already been to the moon.

1929
01:24:28.417 --> 01:24:30.601
[Benji] And now. of course.
all the boys wanna go to Mars.

1930
01:24:30.625 --> 01:24:31.601
Fuck Mars.

1931
01:24:31.625 --> 01:24:33.559
Let's go to that big. orange star

1932
01:24:33.583 --> 01:24:34.934
that we call the sun.

1933
01:24:34.958 --> 01:24:36.018
Totally unexplored!

1934
01:24:36.042 --> 01:24:37.643
We've been looking at it for centuries.

1935
01:24:37.667 --> 01:24:38.643
I'm gonna build a little rocket.

1936
01:24:38.667 --> 01:24:39.726
I'm gonna call it <i>The Icarus</i>.

1937
01:24:39.750 --> 01:24:41.309
Icarus did fly too close to the sun.

1938
01:24:41.333 --> 01:24:43.684
- He did fly too close.
- He did. And he fried.

1939
01:24:43.708 --> 01:24:45.434
That's... You're missing the point. honey.

1940
01:24:45.458 --> 01:24:46.434
[Emily] It's like an irony.

1941
01:24:46.458 --> 01:24:47.768
- [Benji] No. it's not ironic.
- What's going on?

1942
01:24:47.792 --> 01:24:48.934
- [Benji] It's...
- Hmm?

1943
01:24:48.958 --> 01:24:50.500
You look like a nervous cat.

1944
01:24:51.792 --> 01:24:52.792
Uh...

1945
01:24:53.292 --> 01:24:54.684
- Compliment?
- No.

1946
01:24:54.708 --> 01:24:56.643
- Hang on a second.
- Oh. Is it... Is it...

1947
01:24:56.667 --> 01:24:58.184
I don't know. I'll go find out.

1948
01:24:58.208 --> 01:24:59.268
So sorry.

1949
01:24:59.292 --> 01:25:00.500
[in Italian] <i>Scusi.</i>

1950
01:25:11.417 --> 01:25:13.309
[in English] I'm ready to make
an announcement.

1951
01:25:13.333 --> 01:25:14.726
Whenever you're ready.

1952
01:25:14.750 --> 01:25:16.018
[Benji] Oh. we're not closed yet.

1953
01:25:16.042 --> 01:25:17.833
Still ironing out some of the details.

1954
01:25:18.500 --> 01:25:20.208
Oh. I see.

1955
01:25:21.708 --> 01:25:22.833
[sighs]

1956
01:25:25.583 --> 01:25:29.226
So generous what you're doing for Emily.

1957
01:25:29.250 --> 01:25:30.250
Oh.

1958
01:25:32.542 --> 01:25:35.083
[chuckles] I know she has many plans.

1959
01:25:35.833 --> 01:25:39.309
But I do hope that some <i>Runway</i> traditions

1960
01:25:39.333 --> 01:25:40.542
are allowed to remain.

1961
01:25:41.667 --> 01:25:42.667
Hmm.

1962
01:25:43.042 --> 01:25:44.083
Who knows?

1963
01:25:44.583 --> 01:25:46.393
Look. the world
is changing so fast sometimes

1964
01:25:46.417 --> 01:25:48.559
that even I can't comprehend it.

1965
01:25:48.583 --> 01:25:50.042
So tradition. well...

1966
01:25:50.708 --> 01:25:53.018
I think a day is coming.
perhaps very soon.

1967
01:25:53.042 --> 01:25:54.351
where. you know.

1968
01:25:54.375 --> 01:25:55.851
<i>Runway</i> won't need models

1969
01:25:55.875 --> 01:25:58.851
or locations or even designers.

1970
01:25:58.875 --> 01:26:01.143
It'll all just. you know. be AI.

1971
01:26:01.167 --> 01:26:02.684
Mmm. Mmm.

1972
01:26:02.708 --> 01:26:06.726
Surely some things will stay the same.

1973
01:26:06.750 --> 01:26:10.333
A commitment to beauty. artistry.

1974
01:26:11.792 --> 01:26:16.434
the best in human achievement. maybe.

1975
01:26:16.458 --> 01:26:17.458
Maybe.

1976
01:26:18.375 --> 01:26:19.375
But...

1977
01:26:21.792 --> 01:26:22.792
look around you.

1978
01:26:24.625 --> 01:26:27.976
We're in an ancient city
that was once part of

1979
01:26:28.000 --> 01:26:30.601
one of the greatest empires
that the world has ever known.

1980
01:26:30.625 --> 01:26:33.333
Now there's just little traces of it left.

1981
01:26:35.083 --> 01:26:36.643
The world is about change.

1982
01:26:36.667 --> 01:26:38.347
That's what human beings don't understand.

1983
01:26:39.083 --> 01:26:41.417
The future just comes
rushing at us like. um...

1984
01:26:42.250 --> 01:26:44.667
well. like the lava of Pompeii.

1985
01:26:47.083 --> 01:26:48.351
Our job is to just let it take

1986
01:26:48.375 --> 01:26:50.042
what it wants to take. you know?

1987
01:26:50.667 --> 01:26:51.559
One day. it's going to come

1988
01:26:51.583 --> 01:26:53.018
and it's going to smother us all.

1989
01:26:53.042 --> 01:26:55.042
[laughs. snorts]

1990
01:26:56.042 --> 01:26:58.042
And maybe that's the way
it has to be. hmm?

1991
01:27:06.250 --> 01:27:07.250
[softly] Maybe.

1992
01:27:10.917 --> 01:27:12.042
Excuse me.

1993
01:27:23.292 --> 01:27:25.292
[♪ Pensive music playing]

1994
01:28:07.667 --> 01:28:08.875
- Hey.
- [gasps]

1995
01:28:09.833 --> 01:28:11.184
You made it.

1996
01:28:11.208 --> 01:28:12.434
Yeah. sorry.

1997
